Building autossh
================

autossh is a Rust project. Build with:

    cargo build --release

The result is `target/release/autossh`.

The Makefile in this directory is a thin convenience wrapper:

    make            # cargo build --release + copy binary to ./autossh
    make check      # build + run unit + integration tests
    make install    # install binary, manpage, docs and examples
                    # (honors DESTDIR and prefix)

Prerequisites:

    - Rust 1.70 or newer (stable). 1.95+ recommended.
    - A C compiler. The build links a 13-line C shim,
      c-shim/jumpbuf.c, because libc::sigjmp_buf is not exposed
      by the libc 0.2 crate.
    - For `make check`: gcc (the test mocks rely on the
      gcc-specific -Wl,--wrap= linker flag).
